1
00:00:37,450 --> 00:00:40,886
毕尔包,西班牙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

2
00:00:41,921 --> 00:00:45,357
瑞士工业银行
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

3
00:00:48,895 --> 00:00:51,625
庞德先生 谢谢你百忙之中
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So good of you to come see me, Mr. Bond.{\r}

4
00:00:51,831 --> 00:00:54,265
还能抽空赶来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Particularly on such short notice.{\r}

5
00:00:54,901 --> 00:00:58,359
如果信不过瑞士银行家 这世界会变成什么样子？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}lf you can't trust a Swiss banker, what's the world come to?{\r}

6
00:00:59,438 --> 00:01:01,804
既然大家都准备好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And now that we're all comfortable...{\r}

7
00:01:02,108 --> 00:01:03,803
请坐好吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...why don't you sit down?{\r}

8
00:01:05,278 --> 00:01:06,905
我费了点工夫
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It was not easy...{\r}

9
00:01:07,113 --> 00:01:09,206
终于拿回钱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...but I have retrieved the money.{\r}

10
00:01:09,849 --> 00:01:13,307
罗伯爵士一定会很高兴的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No doubt Sir Robert will be pleased to see it again.{\r}

11
00:01:13,553 --> 00:01:17,683
以目前的汇率来计算 扣掉手续费
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}At the current rate of exchange, minus the fees and certain...{\r}

12
00:01:17,924 --> 00:01:19,687
和一些额外费用
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...unforeseeable expenses.{\r}

13
00:01:20,326 --> 00:01:21,793
这就是收据
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Voila, the receipt.{\r}

14
00:01:22,028 --> 00:01:24,155
你要过目吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Would you like to check my figures?{\r}

15
00:01:25,832 --> 00:01:27,595
我确定数字是正确的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sure they're perfectly rounded.{\r}

16
00:01:29,268 --> 00:01:30,758
全都在这儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's all there.{\r}

17
00:01:30,970 --> 00:01:32,528
我不是为钱来的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't come for the money.{\r}

18
00:01:33,639 --> 00:01:35,834
罗伯爵士买的报告
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The report Sir Robert bought was stolen...{\r}

19
00:01:36,042 --> 00:01:38,101
是从一个为它而死的 情报员手中偷来的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...from an Ml6 agent who was killed for it.{\r}

20
00:01:41,714 --> 00:01:43,147
我要知道凶手是谁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to know who killed him.{\r}

21
00:01:43,349 --> 00:01:46,113
-真惨 -我只要名字
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Terrible tragedy. -I just want a name.{\r}

22
00:01:46,352 --> 00:01:49,879
我只是中间人 把钱归还原主
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I am merely the middleman. I'm trying to do the honorable thing...{\r}

23
00:01:50,122 --> 00:01:52,556
算是很有良心了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...returning the money to its rightful owner.{\r}

24
00:01:52,758 --> 00:01:56,194
这对瑞士银行家来说 是多不简单的事啊
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We know how difficult that can be for a Swiss banker.{\r}

25
00:02:01,100 --> 00:02:04,866
我给你机会把钱带走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I am offering you the opportunity to walk out with the money.{\r}

26
00:02:05,338 --> 00:02:08,796
我给你机会把命留下来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I'm giving you the opportunity to walk out with your life.{\r}

27
00:02:09,008 --> 00:02:10,566
照目前的情况看来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Looking at our present situation...{\r}

28
00:02:10,776 --> 00:02:12,437
身为一个银行家,我得说你没有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...as a banker, I'd have to say...{\r}

29
00:02:12,645 --> 00:02:15,205
说这种狠话的本钱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...that the numbers are not on your side.{\r}

30
00:02:16,282 --> 00:02:18,580
也许你没有看到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Perhaps you failed to take into account...{\r}

31
00:02:19,785 --> 00:02:20,752
我潜在的资本
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...my hidden assets.{\r}

32
00:02:31,831 --> 00:02:34,129
现在是我占上风
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You've had a small reversal of fortune.{\r}

33
00:02:35,067 --> 00:02:37,160
-把名字说出来 -办不到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Give me the name. -I can't tell you.{\r}

34
00:02:37,370 --> 00:02:39,031
咱们数到三
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's count to three.{\r}

35
00:02:39,805 --> 00:02:41,568
你一定办得到,对吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can do that, can't you?{\r}

36
00:02:41,841 --> 00:02:42,830
一
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}One.{\r}

37
00:02:44,443 --> 00:02:45,432
二
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Two.{\r}

38
00:02:45,912 --> 00:02:46,936
好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All right.{\r}

39
00:02:47,380 --> 00:02:49,075
不过你得保护我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But you'll have to protect me--{\r}

40
00:04:34,253 --> 00:04:37,279
MI6情报总局 伦敦
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

41
00:04:49,135 --> 00:04:50,193
詹姆斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}James.{\r}

42
00:04:50,403 --> 00:04:52,769
你有没有带礼物送我？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you brought me a souvenir from your trip?{\r}

43
00:04:52,972 --> 00:04:54,030
巧克力？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Chocolates?{\r}

44
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:55,832
订婚戒？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}An engagement ring?{\r}

45
00:04:56,809 --> 00:04:58,674
你一定喜欢这玩意
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I thought you'd enjoy one of these.{\r}

46
00:05:00,079 --> 00:05:01,068
真浪漫
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How romantic.{\r}

47
00:05:03,949 --> 00:05:05,610
我知道该放哪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I know exactly where to put that.{\r}

48
00:05:10,089 --> 00:05:11,647
梦妮
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, Moneypenny.{\r}

49
00:05:11,891 --> 00:05:13,916
就像我俩的关系
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The story of our relationship:{\r}

50
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,253
食之无味,弃之可惜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Close, but no cigar.{\r}

51
00:05:16,962 --> 00:05:21,023
抱歉打扰了,007 请你进来一下？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I hate to tear you away from affairs of state. Would you mind coming in?{\r}

52
00:05:23,035 --> 00:05:24,627
马上来,M夫人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Right away, M.{\r}

53
00:05:26,472 --> 00:05:28,337
罗伯金恩爵士 这是詹姆斯庞德
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir Robert King, James Bond.{\r}

54
00:05:29,542 --> 00:05:33,342
你帮我找回我的钱,谢谢 干得好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The man who retrieved my money. Thank you. Excellent work.{\r}

55
00:05:34,246 --> 00:05:35,941
你要小心,M夫人 我可能会把他挖走的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Be careful, M. I might steal him from you.{\r}

56
00:05:36,449 --> 00:05:39,543
建筑不是我的专长
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Construction's not exactly my specialty.{\r}

57
00:05:39,785 --> 00:05:41,514
事实上,他是专门搞破坏的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Quite the opposite, in fact.{\r}

58
00:05:42,988 --> 00:05:43,818
帮我问候你家人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Best to the family.{\r}

59
00:05:49,228 --> 00:05:50,195
老朋友吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Old friend?{\r}

60
00:05:51,097 --> 00:05:53,065
我们在牛津一起念法律
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We read law at Oxford together.{\r}

61
00:05:54,033 --> 00:05:56,160
我早就知道他会称霸天下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I always knew he'd conquer the world.{\r}

62
00:05:57,169 --> 00:05:58,193
要喝一杯吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Care for a drink?{\r}

63
00:05:58,404 --> 00:05:59,371
好,谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, thank you.{\r}

64
00:06:00,840 --> 00:06:02,831
他的为人很有原则
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's a man of great integrity.{\r}

65
00:06:03,342 --> 00:06:06,505
却花三百万英镑 买失窃报告
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Who buys stolen reports for 3 million pounds.{\r}

66
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:08,137
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}

67
00:06:09,315 --> 00:06:10,509
有狙击手的线索吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Any leads on the sniper?{\r}

68
00:06:11,016 --> 00:06:12,040
没有
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Not one.{\r}

69
00:06:12,384 --> 00:06:13,510
是职业高手做的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Professional job.{\r}

70
00:06:13,986 --> 00:06:15,977
一定受人指使
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She must be working for someone.{\r}

71
00:06:16,489 --> 00:06:18,616
-这就是失窃报告？ -对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Is this the stolen report? -Yes. Classified.{\r}

72
00:06:18,858 --> 00:06:20,723
从苏俄原子能源部来的 机密文件
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}From the Russian Atomic Energy Department.{\r}

73
00:06:20,926 --> 00:06:22,518
金恩要这个干什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What would King want this for?{\r}

74
00:06:23,162 --> 00:06:26,154
他以为这项秘密报告
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was led to believe the document was a secret report...{\r}

75
00:06:26,365 --> 00:06:30,563
指认了个一直在破坏 他新的输油管的恐怖份子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...identifying the terrorists who'd attacked his new oil pipeline.{\r}

76
00:06:31,437 --> 00:06:32,563
有意思
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Interesting.{\r}

77
00:06:34,039 --> 00:06:38,032
但这没解释为什么有人救我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It doesn't explain why someone would want me out of their office alive.{\r}

78
00:06:46,418 --> 00:06:47,783
金恩！那笔钱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}King! The money.{\r}

79
00:06:48,921 --> 00:06:50,411
梦妮,拦住金恩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Moneypenny, stop King.{\r}

80
00:06:58,631 --> 00:06:59,757
让开！让开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Move! Move, move!{\r}

81
00:07:00,266 --> 00:07:01,665
快让开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Get out of the way!{\r}

82
00:07:05,838 --> 00:07:07,135
住手！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}

83
00:07:43,976 --> 00:07:45,068
让开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Move!{\r}

84
00:07:45,277 --> 00:07:46,972
快让开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Get out of the way! Move!{\r}

85
00:07:55,821 --> 00:07:57,254
住手！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop, stop!{\r}

86
00:07:57,456 --> 00:07:59,321
那还没完成呢！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It isn't finished!{\r}

87
00:13:05,197 --> 00:13:06,323
放开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let go!{\r}

88
00:13:06,532 --> 00:13:08,500
-你在干--？ -放开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-What do you think you're--? -Let go!{\r}

89
00:13:37,596 --> 00:13:38,756
听我说！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Listen to me!{\r}

90
00:13:39,398 --> 00:13:40,524
你逃不了的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can't get away.{\r}

91
00:13:41,033 --> 00:13:43,126
跟我合作 说出背后主使
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We can make a deal. Tell me who's behind this...{\r}

92
00:13:43,335 --> 00:13:44,324
你替谁工作？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...who you work for.{\r}

93
00:13:44,836 --> 00:13:45,825
住手！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't do it!{\r}

94
00:13:46,038 --> 00:13:47,403
别把我们炸死！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't blow us up!{\r}

95
00:13:47,673 --> 00:13:48,503
我能保护你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can protect you.{\r}

96
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,865
明白吗？ 谁也不能伤害你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you understand? I can protect you.{\r}

97
00:13:51,343 --> 00:13:52,742
他就能！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Not from him!{\r}

98
00:14:29,448 --> 00:14:32,542
纵横天下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

99
00:17:20,652 --> 00:17:21,812
亲爱的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, my dear.{\r}

100
00:17:34,700 --> 00:17:36,395
那女孩是谁？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Who is that young woman?{\r}

101
00:17:36,969 --> 00:17:38,368
金恩的女儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}King's daughter.{\r}

102
00:17:39,104 --> 00:17:39,934
伊莉翠
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Elektra.{\r}

103
00:17:40,939 --> 00:17:42,031
谢谢
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}

104
00:17:44,876 --> 00:17:46,503
钞票浸过尿素
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The money was dipped in urea.{\r}

105
00:17:46,712 --> 00:17:50,307
-MI6情报局总部苏格兰 -威力强大的肥料炸药
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A highly compacted fertilizer bomb.{\r}

106
00:17:50,515 --> 00:17:52,847
007的手碰过钞票 又摸到冰块
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Having handled the money, the water on 007's hands...{\r}

107
00:17:53,085 --> 00:17:55,747
于是引起化学反应
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...when he touched the ice, started a chemical reaction.{\r}

108
00:17:55,988 --> 00:18:00,015
有一张钞票的反伪造金属线 被换成镁制引信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}In one note, the anti-counterfeiting strip was replaced with magnesium...{\r}

109
00:18:00,258 --> 00:18:03,455
金恩的胸针
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...which acted as a detonator. And King's lapel pin...{\r}

110
00:18:03,662 --> 00:18:05,152
也被换成
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...was switched for a copy...{\r}

111
00:18:05,364 --> 00:18:09,095
引爆炸药的无线电发送器
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...which contained a radio transmitter to trigger the blast.{\r}

112
00:18:09,301 --> 00:18:12,498
换句话说 他引爆炸弹炸死自己的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}In other words, he set off the bomb that killed him.{\r}

113
00:18:13,372 --> 00:18:15,636
我们知道凶手是金恩的亲信
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We know it was someone close to King...{\r}

114
00:18:16,308 --> 00:18:19,004
唯一的线索却 在气球上自杀身亡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and our only lead committed suicide on that balloon.{\r}

115
00:18:19,511 --> 00:18:21,672
金恩企业规模如此庞大
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But given the size of King's organization...{\r}

116
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,212
想找出凶手 简直就是海底捞针
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...it could be anyone, anywhere.{\r}

117
00:18:29,087 --> 00:18:30,952
绝不能饶过他们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This will not stand.{\r}

118
00:18:31,957 --> 00:18:35,222
不能让一个懦夫 利用我们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We won't be terrorized by cowards who'd murder an innocent man...{\r}

119
00:18:35,427 --> 00:18:36,860
残杀无辜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and use us as the tool.{\r}

120
00:18:37,129 --> 00:18:39,120
我们一定要找出凶手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll find those who committed this atrocity.{\r}

121
00:18:39,331 --> 00:18:42,892
就算追到天涯海角
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll follow them to the farthest ends of the earth, if needs be.{\r}

122
00:18:43,735 --> 00:18:46,135
也要将他们绳之以法
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And we will bring them to justice.{\r}

123
00:18:59,451 --> 00:19:00,315
谭纳！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tanner!{\r}

124
00:19:00,552 --> 00:19:04,716
M夫人说你不能参与行动 除非得到医生批准
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}M says you're off the active-duty list until you're cleared by medical.{\r}

125
00:19:10,362 --> 00:19:11,989
锁骨脱臼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Dislocated collarbone.{\r}

126
00:19:12,197 --> 00:19:16,190
要是扯断韧带 你就得休养好几星期
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}If any more tendons snap, I'm afraid you'll be out of action for weeks.{\r}

127
