382
00:41:53,724 --> 00:41:54,782
你在这儿很安全
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You'll be safe here.{\r}

383
00:41:55,459 --> 00:41:57,188
我不想要安全
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't want to be safe.{\r}

384
00:42:04,468 --> 00:42:05,992
我很快就会回来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll be back soon.{\r}

385
00:42:08,172 --> 00:42:10,663
现在到底谁在害怕 庞德先生？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And who's afraid now, Mr. Bond?{\r}

386
00:43:22,613 --> 00:43:24,945
我要见魏伦汀苏考斯基
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to see Valentin Zukovsky.{\r}

387
00:43:25,249 --> 00:43:26,580
不可能
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Impossible.{\r}

388
00:43:27,885 --> 00:43:29,250
伏特加马丁尼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Vodka martini.{\r}

389
00:43:29,786 --> 00:43:31,344
用摇的,别用搅的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Shaken, not stirred.{\r}

390
00:43:33,423 --> 00:43:35,448
就说詹姆斯庞德找他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell him James Bond is here.{\r}

391
00:43:36,860 --> 00:43:38,020
快去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Now.{\r}

392
00:43:43,767 --> 00:43:45,860
我看你是没听清楚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think you heard me.{\r}

393
00:43:55,412 --> 00:43:58,108
苏先生很乐意见你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Zukovsky would be delighted to see you.{\r}

394
00:44:03,053 --> 00:44:03,917
你先请
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}After you.{\r}

395
00:44:05,989 --> 00:44:07,115
不,你先请
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}After you.{\r}

396
00:44:08,158 --> 00:44:09,090
我坚持
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I insist.{\r}

397
00:44:12,362 --> 00:44:13,954
你也来一点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And a little for you.{\r}

398
00:44:17,234 --> 00:44:19,031
庞德！詹姆斯庞德！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bond! James Bond!{\r}

399
00:44:19,736 --> 00:44:21,033
这是妮娜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Meet Nina.{\r}

400
00:44:21,538 --> 00:44:22,971
和薇洛丝卡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And Verushka.{\r}

401
00:44:24,341 --> 00:44:26,172
叫她们走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Lose the girls, Valentin.{\r}

402
00:44:26,376 --> 00:44:27,570
我们得谈谈
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We need to talk.{\r}

403
00:44:28,078 --> 00:44:32,447
我为什么突然觉得 我买的保险还不够？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why am I suddenly worried that I'm not carrying enough insurance?{\r}

404
00:44:32,649 --> 00:44:34,048
别紧张,老詹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Chill out, James.{\r}

405
00:44:38,522 --> 00:44:39,454
好吧,各位
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Fine, ladies.{\r}

406
00:44:39,656 --> 00:44:40,953
快滚！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go on. Beat it. Scram.{\r}

407
00:44:41,158 --> 00:44:43,092
蛮牛,把钱给她们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bull, give them an inch.{\r}

408
00:44:50,234 --> 00:44:53,135
要确定她们在我赌场都输光
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And make sure they lose it in this casino.{\r}

409
00:44:55,305 --> 00:44:57,205
后会有期,庞德先生
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll see you later, Mr. Bond.{\r}

410
00:44:57,407 --> 00:44:59,671
你的钱都存在你的嘴巴里
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I see you put your money where your mouth is.{\r}

411
00:45:00,477 --> 00:45:02,741
蛮牛信不过银行
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Bullion does not trust banks.{\r}

412
00:45:02,946 --> 00:45:05,107
你想聊什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So what would you like to talk about?{\r}

413
00:45:05,315 --> 00:45:07,340
我恐怕帮不上忙
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm not sure I can really help you.{\r}

414
00:45:07,551 --> 00:45:09,576
我现在都做合法生意
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm a legitimate businessman now.{\r}

415
00:45:11,321 --> 00:45:15,087
来点我的苏氏极品鱼子酱？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Would you care for some caviar? My own brand: Zukovsky's Finest.{\r}

416
00:45:16,393 --> 00:45:17,360
你看看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look at this.{\r}

417
00:45:20,530 --> 00:45:22,555
苏俄特种部队
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Russian Special Services.{\r}

418
00:45:23,834 --> 00:45:26,268
原子能源部的反恐怖份子单位
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Atomic Energy Antiterrorist Unit.{\r}

419
00:45:26,470 --> 00:45:27,960
哪儿找到的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Where did you find this?{\r}

420
00:45:28,171 --> 00:45:31,937
我从一个今早想刺杀 伊莉翠金恩的人的身上拿到的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I took it off a Parahawk which tried to kill Elektra King this morning.{\r}

421
00:45:32,909 --> 00:45:34,604
幕后主使是雷纳
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Renard is behind this.{\r}

422
00:45:39,883 --> 00:45:42,477
咱们最好先喝一杯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I think you and I had better have a drink.{\r}

423
00:45:48,525 --> 00:45:51,085
阿富汗事件后 KGB认为
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And then after Afghanistan, the KGB decided...{\r}

424
00:45:51,295 --> 00:45:54,458
雷纳太危险 于是把他开除
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...Renard was a liability and just cut him loose.{\r}

425
00:45:54,665 --> 00:45:56,428
他现在独立作业
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Now he works freelance.{\r}

426
00:45:56,633 --> 00:45:58,191
他替谁工作？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But for whom?{\r}

427
00:45:59,269 --> 00:46:01,203
四条输油管互相竞争
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There are four competing pipelines.{\r}

428
00:46:01,405 --> 00:46:04,670
我打赌这里有一半的赌客
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm willing to bet half the customers in this casino would be...{\r}

429
00:46:04,875 --> 00:46:07,639
都想金恩输油管消失
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...very happy to see the King pipeline disappear.{\r}

430
00:46:09,446 --> 00:46:11,607
-有什么好笑？ -没什么,只是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-What's funny? -Nothing. It appears...{\r}

431
00:46:11,815 --> 00:46:14,613
金小姐很大胆
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...Miss King does not share your concern.{\r}

432
00:46:22,292 --> 00:46:23,919
你来这儿干嘛？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing here?{\r}

433
00:46:24,261 --> 00:46:25,990
跟你一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The same thing you are.{\r}

434
00:46:26,196 --> 00:46:28,596
找出想杀我的歹徒
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Looking for the people who tried to kill me.{\r}

435
00:46:28,799 --> 00:46:30,926
让我现在就带你回家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me take you home. Now.{\r}

436
00:46:31,134 --> 00:46:34,069
不,我要证明我不怕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No. I want them to see I'm not frightened.{\r}

437
00:46:34,271 --> 00:46:37,035
金小姐,很高兴见到你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Miss King, how very nice to see you.{\r}

438
00:46:37,474 --> 00:46:39,374
我免费为你保留了令尊的位子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We've kept your father's chair free.{\r}

439
00:46:39,576 --> 00:46:42,067
免费？ 拜托,这里什么都要钱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Free? Nothing comes free from you.{\r}

440
00:46:43,547 --> 00:46:47,039
令尊有一百万美元的信用
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your father had a credit line with us. One million U.S.{\r}

441
00:46:47,384 --> 00:46:49,909
你也一样有这个特权
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd be happy to extend you that courtesy.{\r}

442
00:46:54,057 --> 00:46:55,319
你想玩点什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So what's it to be?{\r}

443
00:46:57,494 --> 00:46:59,553
21点,令尊的最爱？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Blackjack, your father's favorite?{\r}

444
00:47:00,397 --> 00:47:01,989
咱们干脆一点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's keep it simple.{\r}

445
00:47:02,999 --> 00:47:04,330
一翻两瞪眼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}One card.{\r}

446
00:47:04,534 --> 00:47:05,728
赌大一点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}High draw.{\r}

447
00:47:09,339 --> 00:47:10,237
一百万元
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A million dollars.{\r}

448
00:47:14,611 --> 00:47:15,543
等等
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wait.{\r}

449
00:47:16,446 --> 00:47:18,505
前三张抽掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bury the top three cards.{\r}

450
00:47:20,717 --> 00:47:22,810
你下定决心想保护我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're determined to protect me.{\r}

451
00:47:23,053 --> 00:47:25,021
你太任性了 别这么做
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}From yourself. You don't have to do this.{\r}

452
00:47:27,891 --> 00:47:31,452
如果不能随心所欲 活着也没有意义
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no point in living if you can't feel alive.{\r}

453
00:47:43,707 --> 00:47:44,605
红心皇后
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Queen of hearts.{\r}

454
00:47:57,888 --> 00:47:59,446
你碰上了克星
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It appears you've been beaten...{\r}

455
00:48:01,124 --> 00:48:02,887
黑桃A
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...by the ace of clubs.{\r}

456
00:48:07,063 --> 00:48:08,553
别难过,亲爱的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No hard feelings, my dear.{\r}

457
00:48:08,765 --> 00:48:10,289
下次再来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come again soon.{\r}

458
00:48:16,206 --> 00:48:17,468
走了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Shall we?{\r}

459
00:48:21,411 --> 00:48:23,845
我玩不起这种游戏
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is a game I can't afford to play.{\r}

460
00:48:26,116 --> 00:48:27,276
我知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I know.{\r}

461
00:48:30,520 --> 00:48:33,921
-大卫朵夫呢？ -我放他一晚的假
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-What happened to Davidov? -I gave him the night off.{\r}

462
00:48:55,979 --> 00:48:57,947
欢迎光临魔鬼窟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Welcome to the Devil's Breath.{\r}

463
00:48:59,783 --> 00:49:03,116
数千年来印度朝圣者 前来此地
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}For thousands of years, Hindu pilgrims journeyed to this holy place...{\r}

464
00:49:05,055 --> 00:49:08,616
见识永不熄灭的神迹之火
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...to witness the wonder of the natural flames that never die...{\r}

465
00:49:09,893 --> 00:49:11,918
他们为了证明
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and to test their devotion...{\r}

466
00:49:12,996 --> 00:49:14,020
对神的信仰
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...to God...{\r}

467
00:49:15,532 --> 00:49:18,524
一边握住滚烫的石块
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...by holding the scalding rocks in their hands...{\r}

468
00:49:21,538 --> 00:49:23,233
一边向神祷告
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...as they said their prayers.{\r}

469
00:49:25,342 --> 00:49:26,468
大卫朵夫,告诉我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell me, Davidov...{\r}

470
00:49:27,377 --> 00:49:29,106
今天下午出了什么事？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...what happened this afternoon?{\r}

471
00:49:29,312 --> 00:49:31,143
你保证过给我最顶尖的手下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You promised me your best men.{\r}

472
00:49:31,348 --> 00:49:33,407
艾考夫提供最新的武器
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Arkov supplied the latest weapons.{\r}

473
00:49:33,617 --> 00:49:35,107
没错,可是庞德…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, but Bond--{\r}

474
00:49:35,318 --> 00:49:36,842
庞德手无寸铁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bond was unarmed.{\r}

475
00:49:39,022 --> 00:49:42,549
你呢,艾考夫？ 都准备好了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And you, Arkov? Is everything ready for tomorrow?{\r}

476
00:49:42,792 --> 00:49:45,352
授权书和通行证在车上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have the authorization and passes in the car.{\r}

477
00:49:45,562 --> 00:49:48,087
飞机今晚就到 不过…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have arranged for a plane tonight, but....{\r}

478
00:49:48,632 --> 00:49:49,690
不过什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But what?{\r}

479
00:49:49,900 --> 00:49:52,733
我们应该取消其它的任务
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We should scrub the rest of the mission.{\r}

480
00:49:52,936 --> 00:49:55,962
攻击直升机应该回去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The Parahawks were meant to be returned.{\r}

481
00:49:56,172 --> 00:49:58,299
别人会对我起疑心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}People will ask questions, even of me.{\r}

482
00:49:58,508 --> 00:50:00,874
都是因为他的无能
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All because of his incompetence.{\r}

483
00:50:01,077 --> 00:50:01,975
我明白了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I see.{\r}

484
00:50:02,178 --> 00:50:04,612
你说得对 应该惩罚他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I see you're right. He should be punished.{\r}

485
00:50:06,049 --> 00:50:07,914
大卫朵夫,拿着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Davidov, hold this for me.{\r}

486
00:50:12,022 --> 00:50:14,752
我太高估你了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It was wrong of me to expect so much of you.{\r}

487
00:50:16,660 --> 00:50:17,820
杀了他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Kill him.{\r}

488
00:50:20,063 --> 00:50:22,258
他不够忠心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He failed his test of devotion.{\r}

489
00:50:25,835 --> 00:50:27,496
你可以坐他的位子
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can take his place.{\r}

490
00:50:27,837 --> 00:50:29,327
你可以取代他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Take his I.D.{\r}

491
00:50:31,241 --> 00:50:32,868
但一定要准时
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And do be on time.{\r}

492
00:50:52,796 --> 00:50:54,229
你的肩膀受伤了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Poor shoulder.{\r}

493
00:50:55,599 --> 00:50:56,964
一定很痛
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It looks painful.{\r}

494
00:50:59,836 --> 00:51:01,861
得多照顾点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It needs constant attention.{\r}

495
00:51:05,909 --> 00:51:06,967
我知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I knew....{\r}

496
00:51:07,644 --> 00:51:09,669
我第一次见到你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I knew when I first saw you.{\r}

497
00:51:10,747 --> 00:51:12,806
我就知道事情会这样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I knew it would be like this.{\r}

498
00:51:25,462 --> 00:51:27,259
这些冰块够了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Enough ice for one day.{\r}

499
00:51:47,384 --> 00:51:49,147
你怎么活下来？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How did you survive?{\r}

500
00:51:56,726 --> 00:51:58,523
我色诱守卫
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I seduced the guards.{\r}

501
00:51:58,762 --> 00:51:59,694
用我的身体
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Used my body.{\r}

502
00:52:01,031 --> 00:52:02,692
把他制伏
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It gave me control.{\r}

503
00:52:04,734 --> 00:52:07,931
然后拿了枪就扫射
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And the rest, I got a gun and started shooting.{\r}

504
00:52:11,474 --> 00:52:12,907
你呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And what about you?{\r}

505
00:52:13,109 --> 00:52:14,974
你是怎么活下来的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you do to survive?{\r}

506
00:52:19,282 --> 00:52:20,749
我在美女身上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I take pleasure...{\r}

507
00:52:22,919 --> 00:52:24,409
寻找乐趣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...in great beauty.{\r}

508
00:55:03,646 --> 00:55:05,614
走吧,时候不早了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go. It's getting late.{\r}

509
00:55:11,187 --> 00:55:12,848
大卫朵夫呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What happened to Davidov?{\r}

510
00:55:13,089 --> 00:55:14,886
他不是要来吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I was told to expect him.{\r}

511
00:55:16,125 --> 00:55:18,093
他被埋在工作堆中
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was buried with work.{\r}

512
00:55:19,495 --> 00:55:21,463
走吧,把你的东西带着
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go. Get your stuff.{\r}

513
00:55:33,343 --> 00:55:34,674
咱们出发吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay, come on.{\r}

514
00:55:34,878 --> 00:55:36,436
走吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's get out of here.{\r}

515
00:55:38,548 --> 00:55:39,537
你迟到了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're late.{\r}

516
00:55:39,883 --> 00:55:41,316
带来了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you bring it?{\r}

517
00:55:41,818 --> 00:55:42,785
礼物呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The grease.{\r}

518
00:55:46,289 --> 00:55:47,256
当然
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course.{\r}

519
00:55:54,964 --> 00:55:55,862
太好了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Excellent.{\r}

520
00:56:13,683 --> 00:56:15,776
准备好,十分钟后开始
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Get ready. We're 1 0 minutes out.{\r}

521
00:56:16,286 --> 00:56:18,254
记得戴上通行证
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But make sure you wear the I.D.{\r}

522
00:56:34,804 --> 00:56:38,467
哈萨克 中亚
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

523
00:57:04,567 --> 00:57:06,330
我出去透透气
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm gonna go get some air.{\r}

524
00:57:24,087 --> 00:57:28,023
欢迎,艾考夫博士 我很景仰您的研究
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Welcome to Kazakhstan, Dr. Arkov. I'm a great admirer of your research.{\r}

525
00:57:28,458 --> 00:57:31,393
这儿很少见到您这种大人物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not often we see someone of your stature here.{\r}

526
00:57:31,594 --> 00:57:33,459
这是我的职责
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I go where the work takes me.{\r}

527
00:57:34,364 --> 00:57:36,855
你的运输证明呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}By the way, you have the transport documents?{\r}

528
00:57:46,142 --> 00:57:48,576
我从核弹里取出钸元素
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I pulled the plutonium out of the one inside.{\r}

529
00:57:48,778 --> 00:57:50,746
可以引爆了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can detonate the triggers now.{\r}

530
00:57:54,751 --> 00:57:57,219
她是拆除核弹专家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, our IDA physicist.{\r}

531
00:57:57,720 --> 00:57:59,620
省点力气 她对男人没兴趣
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't bother. Not interested in men.{\r}

532
00:58:00,323 --> 00:58:01,255
相信我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Take my word for it.{\r}

533
00:58:02,191 --> 00:58:05,752
今年出四次任务 她都没闹绯闻
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This year we decommissioned four test sites. Not even a glimmer.{\r}

534
00:58:10,566 --> 00:58:12,033
你来这儿有事？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you here for a reason?{\r}

535
00:58:12,235 --> 00:58:14,635
还是想闹绯闻？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Or are you just hoping for a glimmer?{\r}

536
00:58:15,071 --> 00:58:15,935
你是哪位？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And you are...?{\r}

537
00:58:16,339 --> 00:58:19,365
米盖艾考夫 苏俄原子能源部
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Mikhail Arkov. Russian Atomic Energy Department.{\r}

538
00:58:20,176 --> 00:58:21,074
小姐是…？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Miss...?{\r}

539
00:58:21,711 --> 00:58:22,905
琼斯博士
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Doctor...{\r}

540
00:58:23,112 --> 00:58:24,841
克莉莫丝琼斯
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...Jones. Christmas Jones.{\r}

541
00:58:25,048 --> 00:58:27,539
别拿我的名字开玩笑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And don't make any jokes. I've heard them all.{\r}

542
00:58:28,351 --> 00:58:30,251
我不知道任何 关于博士的玩笑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know any doctor jokes.{\r}

543
00:58:32,822 --> 00:58:35,120
没问题 搭电梯下去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is okay. Take the elevator down the hole.{\r}

544
00:58:35,324 --> 00:58:37,292
你朋友已经在下面了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your friends are already down there.{\r}

545
00:58:37,827 --> 00:58:39,590
不必穿防护衣吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't I get some protection?{\r}

546
00:58:40,296 --> 00:58:41,957
不必,艾考夫博士
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No, Dr. Arkov.{\r}

547
00:58:42,165 --> 00:58:45,032
下面的钸元素很安全
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Down there it's weapons-grade plutonium. Reasonably safe.{\r}

548
00:58:45,468 --> 00:58:48,198
上面有你们的俄制氢弹 漏出的氢元素
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Up here we have leaking hydrogen bombs that your lab built...{\r}

549
00:58:48,404 --> 00:58:51,066
这半年来我一直都在处理
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...which I've spent the last six months cleaning up.{\r}

550
00:58:51,274 --> 00:58:54,107
你要怕的应该是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So if you need any protection at all, it's from me.{\r}

551
00:58:56,779 --> 00:58:58,474
你的同事在等你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your friends are waiting for you.{\r}

552
00:59:04,487 --> 00:59:05,317
博士
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Doctor.{\r}

553
00:59:08,024 --> 00:59:09,582
你忘了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Aren't you forgetting?{\r}

554
00:59:10,193 --> 00:59:12,855
离开时请归还辐射标签
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

555
00:59:13,329 --> 00:59:14,591
没错,谢谢你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course. Thank you.{\r}

556
00:59:15,364 --> 00:59:16,524
对了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}By the way....{\r}

557
00:59:16,966 --> 00:59:20,732
以苏俄人来说 你的英文说得不错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

558
00:59:22,138 --> 00:59:24,629
我读过牛津大学
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

559
01:00:35,400 --> 01:00:36,799
你在等大卫朵夫吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Expecting Davidov?{\r}

560
01:00:37,402 --> 01:00:40,303
他吃了子弹,来不成
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He caught a bullet instead of the plane.{\r}

561
01:00:40,506 --> 01:00:41,336
下来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Get off.{\r}

562
01:00:41,607 --> 01:00:43,074
给我闭嘴
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Keep your mouth shut.{\r}

563
01:00:44,143 --> 01:00:46,338
我早就死了 你杀不了我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You can't kill me. I'm already dead.{\r}

564
01:00:47,713 --> 01:00:49,544
我看你还没死透
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Not dead enough for me.{\r}

565
01:00:50,048 --> 01:00:51,675
你应该感谢我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Show a little gratitude.{\r}

566
01:00:51,984 --> 01:00:54,350
我在银行家的办公室救了你一命
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I did spare your life at the banker's office.{\r}

567
01:00:55,120 --> 01:00:56,348
没错
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That's right.{\r}

568
01:00:56,889 --> 01:00:59,414
我不能让你死 你那时候在替我工作
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I couldn't kill you. You were working for me.{\r}

569
01:01:00,159 --> 01:01:01,717
你把钱带回去 炸死金恩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You delivered the money, killed King.{\r}

570
01:01:02,427 --> 01:01:03,917
现在你又把飞机带来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Now you brought me the plane.{\r}

571
01:01:04,830 --> 01:01:06,320
你偷走核弹有什么计划？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's your plan for the bomb?{\r}

572
01:01:07,166 --> 01:01:09,566
你先说 还是你根本就没计划？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You first. Or could it be you don't have a plan?{\r}

573
01:01:10,903 --> 01:01:13,167
核弹得留下来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That bomb will never leave this room.{\r}

574
01:01:14,139 --> 01:01:15,163
你也一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Neither will you.{\r}

575
01:01:21,180 --> 01:01:23,648
被一个搞不清楚状况的人威胁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How sad to be threatened by a man...{\r}

576
01:01:23,849 --> 01:01:25,874
真可悲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...who can't grasp what he's involved in.{\r}

577
01:01:26,385 --> 01:01:29,411
什么都不信的人只会报仇
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Revenge is not hard to fathom for a man who believes in nothing.{\r}

578
01:01:29,621 --> 01:01:31,145
你相信什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And what do you believe in?{\r}

579
01:01:31,356 --> 01:01:32,823
贪婪的资本主义？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Preservation of capital?{\r}

580
01:01:33,025 --> 01:01:34,754
尽管开枪吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go ahead, shoot me.{\r}

581
01:01:35,194 --> 01:01:36,525
我才不怕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I welcome it.{\r}

582
01:01:36,795 --> 01:01:39,263
我的手下听见之后会杀了你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My men will hear the shot and kill you.{\r}

583
01:01:39,464 --> 01:01:42,558
然后军队会赶来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And the firefight will bring down half the army from above.{\r}

584
01:01:42,768 --> 01:01:45,760
我在二十分钟内没打电话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But when a certain phone call isn't made in 20 minutes...{\r}

585
01:01:46,104 --> 01:01:47,264
伊莉翠就没命
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...Elektra dies.{\r}

586
01:01:50,142 --> 01:01:51,109
你在唬人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're bluffing.{\r}

587
01:01:52,377 --> 01:01:54,311
她很美,对吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She's beautiful, isn't she?{\r}

588
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:56,580
可惜你不是她的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You should have had her before...{\r}

589
01:01:57,149 --> 01:01:58,878
第一个男人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...when she was innocent.{\r}

590
01:01:59,284 --> 01:02:00,216
我替你开了她的苞
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How does it feel...{\r}

591
01:02:01,153 --> 01:02:03,212
的感觉怎样？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...to know I broke her in for you?{\r}

592
01:02:05,290 --> 01:02:07,781
我通常不杀手无寸铁的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I usually hate killing an unarmed man.{\r}

593
01:02:07,993 --> 01:02:09,756
冷血杀手不好当
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Cold-blooded murder is a filthy business.{\r}

594
01:02:09,962 --> 01:02:12,294
我也厌倦了被处决
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A man tires of being executed.{\r}

595
01:02:13,365 --> 01:02:15,595
不过我对你没感觉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But in your case, I feel nothing...{\r}

596
01:02:15,968 --> 01:02:16,992
就跟你一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...just like you.{\r}

597
01:02:17,202 --> 01:02:20,933
如果不能随心所欲 活着也没有意义
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But then again, there's no point living if you can't feel alive.{\r}

598
01:02:26,278 --> 01:02:28,439
-把枪放下！ -上校,走开！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Drop the gun! -Keep away, colonel.{\r}

599
01:02:28,680 --> 01:02:31,444
他是冒牌货 艾考夫博士已经63岁
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's an impostor. Dr. Arkov is 63 years old.{\r}

600
01:02:31,650 --> 01:02:33,083
他和飞机上的人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is your impostor.{\r}

601
01:02:33,318 --> 01:02:35,616
才是冒牌货
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Along with the men outside on the plane.{\r}

602
01:02:35,821 --> 01:02:36,845
他们想要偷走核弹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They'll steal the bomb.{\r}

603
01:02:39,057 --> 01:02:40,649
我叫你把枪放下！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I said drop it!{\r}

604
01:02:51,536 --> 01:02:52,628
跪下来！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}On your knees!{\r}

605
01:02:55,774 --> 01:02:56,570
干得好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Well done.{\r}

606
01:02:59,144 --> 01:03:00,611
他一定会杀死我们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He would've killed us all.{\r}

607
01:03:01,446 --> 01:03:02,640
你跟他讲过话？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you speak to him?{\r}

608
01:03:02,881 --> 01:03:05,441
对,他不是核能科学家
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, but he's no atomic scientist.{\r}

609
01:03:06,919 --> 01:03:09,444
我想是你允许他下来的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I suppose you were the one who allowed him down.{\r}

610
01:03:18,830 --> 01:03:19,888
你逮到我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You had me...{\r}

611
01:03:21,566 --> 01:03:23,090
不过我早知道你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...but I knew you couldn't...{\r}

612
01:03:23,302 --> 01:03:25,429
肩负不了重任
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...shoulder the responsibility.{\r}

613
01:03:31,877 --> 01:03:34,107
我们继续吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Without any interruptions, let's proceed.{\r}

614
01:03:35,180 --> 01:03:37,774
生面孔太多 包括你的在内
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Too many new faces are here, including yours.{\r}

615
01:03:39,584 --> 01:03:42,849
在我满意之前,核弹就留在这
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The bomb doesn't move until I am satisfied.{\r}

616
01:03:43,522 --> 01:03:45,683
全都给我上去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}All of you, to the surface, now.{\r}

617
01:04:08,113 --> 01:04:09,011
快点,快走！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on! Go!{\r}

618
01:04:12,050 --> 01:04:13,017
快走！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Move!{\r}

619
01:04:20,092 --> 01:04:21,423
我们被封住了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They're sealing us in.{\r}

620
01:04:23,962 --> 01:04:25,122
你是什么人？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Who are you?{\r}

621
01:04:26,231 --> 01:04:28,096
我替英国政府工作
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I work for the British government.{\r}

622
01:04:32,971 --> 01:04:33,835
保持冷静
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Stay calm.{\r}

623
01:06:37,829 --> 01:06:40,127
别生气,庞德
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No hard feelings, Mr. Bond...{\r}

624
01:06:40,332 --> 01:06:41,663
咱们扯平了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...but we're even.{\r}

625
01:06:41,867 --> 01:06:43,095
很快
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Soon...{\r}

626
01:06:43,602 --> 01:06:45,593
你就会没有感觉的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...you'll feel nothing at all.{\r}

627
01:07:11,496 --> 01:07:13,794
把门封住！快！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Seal the door! Close it!{\r}

628
01:07:26,578 --> 01:07:27,545
快！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on!{\r}

629
01:07:48,733 --> 01:07:50,860
继续跑,快！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Keep going! Move! Hang on!{\r}

630
01:07:51,703 --> 01:07:53,762
你这英国的间谍叫什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You're a British spy. Do you have a name?{\r}

631
01:07:53,972 --> 01:07:55,132
庞德
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The name's Bond.{\r}

632
01:08:00,579 --> 01:08:01,876
詹姆斯庞德
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}James Bond.{\r}

633
01:08:12,224 --> 01:08:14,351
别停下来！快跳！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't stop! Go, go! Jump!{\r}

634
01:08:35,447 --> 01:08:36,937
他们跑不远
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They won't get very far.{\r}

635
01:08:37,182 --> 01:08:38,843
核子弹头都有定位晶片
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Every warhead has a locator card.{\r}

636
01:08:39,050 --> 01:08:40,881
我们可以追踪讯号
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We can track the signal.{\r}

637
01:08:42,320 --> 01:08:43,981
你是说这个吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You mean one of these?{\r}

638
01:08:51,663 --> 01:08:53,756
雷纳的飞机在哪儿？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do we have the range of Renard's plane?{\r}

639
01:08:53,965 --> 01:08:56,763
可能在苏俄
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Anywhere in this circle: Russia...{\r}

640
01:08:56,968 --> 01:08:59,300
亚美尼亚,伊朗 哈萨克…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...Armenia, Iran, Kazakhstan, Uzbekistan--{\r}

641
01:08:59,504 --> 01:09:01,995
抱歉打搅了 伊莉翠从巴库打来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry to interrupt. Elektra is calling from Baku.{\r}

642
01:09:02,207 --> 01:09:03,435
她用影像电话
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's on the video line.{\r}

643
01:09:03,675 --> 01:09:05,575
放到大荧幕上
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Put her on the wall screen.{\r}

644
01:09:09,948 --> 01:09:13,076
对不起 我不想烦你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry. I would never call you except...{\r}

645
01:09:13,285 --> 01:09:14,582
不过詹姆斯失踪了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...James has disappeared.{\r}

646
01:09:15,387 --> 01:09:18,447
他在半夜离开我的别墅
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He left my villa in the middle of the night...{\r}

647
01:09:19,824 --> 01:09:23,123
我的安全主任
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and my head of security has been found...{\r}

648
01:09:23,328 --> 01:09:26,092
在机场附近遇害
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...near a local airstrip, murdered.{\r}

649
01:09:27,065 --> 01:09:28,657
我派人过去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll send someone out.{\r}

650
01:09:29,467 --> 01:09:30,559
M夫人,你能来吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}M, could you come?{\r}

651
01:09:31,803 --> 01:09:33,634
我很担心
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't help thinking...{\r}

652
01:09:34,372 --> 01:09:35,703
下一个就是我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...I'm next.{\r}

653
01:09:40,045 --> 01:09:41,137
马上送我过去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Get me out there.{\r}

654
01:09:41,379 --> 01:09:43,677
快送我过去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Just get me out there.{\r}

655
01:10:02,033 --> 01:10:03,159
贾柏？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Gabor?{\r}

656
01:10:14,913 --> 01:10:16,073
你很惊？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Surprised?{\r}

657
01:10:16,581 --> 01:10:18,742
怎么了？ 你疯了吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's wrong with you? Are you crazy?{\r}

658
01:10:18,950 --> 01:10:19,974
也许吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe.{\r}

659
01:10:20,685 --> 01:10:21,777
也许我该问你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe I should ask you.{\r}

660
01:10:22,687 --> 01:10:23,517
毕竟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}After all...{\r}

661
01:10:24,322 --> 01:10:26,790
如果不能随心所欲 活着也没有意义
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...''There's no point in living if you can't feel alive.''{\r}

662
01:10:26,991 --> 01:10:29,653
这不是你的座右铭吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't that right, Elektra? Isn't that your motto?{\r}

663
01:10:30,061 --> 01:10:30,891
你在讲什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you mean?{\r}

664
01:10:31,096 --> 01:10:33,929
还是你老友雷纳教你的？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Or did you steal it from your old friend Renard?{\r}

665
01:10:34,699 --> 01:10:38,260
我跟他聊了一下 他连我的肩伤在哪都知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He and I had a chat. Knew all about us. Knew about my shoulder.{\r}

666
01:10:38,470 --> 01:10:40,028
知道怎么弄痛我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Knew exactly where to hurt me.{\r}

667
01:10:40,238 --> 01:10:42,502
你是说雷纳想杀我？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Renard's the man who's trying to kill me?{\r}

668
01:10:42,707 --> 01:10:43,799
少装了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Drop the act.{\r}

669
01:10:45,443 --> 01:10:46,432
别再演戏了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's over.{\r}

670
01:10:48,046 --> 01:10:49,240
我不知道你在说什么
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know what you mean.{\r}

671
01:10:49,547 --> 01:10:51,014
你清楚得很
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, I think you do.{\r}

672
01:10:53,251 --> 01:10:55,344
这叫做“斯德哥尔摩症候群”
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's called Stockholm syndrome.{\r}

673
01:10:56,554 --> 01:10:58,419
绑架受害人的通病
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Common in kidnappings.{\r}

674
01:10:58,923 --> 01:11:01,050
受害人通常年轻天真
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Young, impressionable victim.{\r}

675
01:11:01,626 --> 01:11:02,888
平日受到百般呵护
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sheltered.{\r}

676
01:11:04,329 --> 01:11:06,820
没有性经验
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sexually inexperienced.{\r}

677
01:11:07,365 --> 01:11:11,199
手段高明的绑匪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}A powerful kidnapper skilled in torture, manipulation.{\r}

678
01:11:12,704 --> 01:11:15,036
受害人突然念头一闪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Something snaps in the victim's mind.{\r}

679
01:11:15,673 --> 01:11:17,538
受害人爱上绑匪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The captive falls in love with her captor.{\r}

680
01:11:18,176 --> 01:11:18,972
胡说八道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How dare you?{\r}

681
01:11:20,245 --> 01:11:21,177
简直胡说八道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How dare you?{\r}

682
01:11:21,579 --> 01:11:23,376
那个禽兽都不如的东西？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That animal. That monster?{\r}

683
01:11:23,915 --> 01:11:25,746
他令我作呕
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He disgusts me.{\r}

684
01:11:26,751 --> 01:11:28,446
你也一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You disgust me.{\r}

685
01:11:29,354 --> 01:11:32,221
他知道你的肩伤,是吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So he knew where to hurt you, is that it?{\r}

686
01:11:32,524 --> 01:11:34,890
你在丧礼上带着吊腕带
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You had a sling on your arm at the funeral.{\r}

687
01:11:35,527 --> 01:11:38,223
我不需要跟你上床也知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I didn't have to sleep with you to find that out.{\r}

688
01:11:38,430 --> 01:11:39,761
他也这么说
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He used your exact words.{\r}

689
01:11:39,964 --> 01:11:41,295
你早就知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So you knew.{\r}

690
01:11:41,900 --> 01:11:44,926
你也知道他一直想杀我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You knew all the time he was out there, coming for me...{\r}

691
01:11:45,136 --> 01:11:46,103
你却欺骗我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and you lied.{\r}

692
01:11:47,172 --> 01:11:48,605
你利用我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You used me.{\r}

693
01:11:49,240 --> 01:11:51,140
你利用我当诱饵
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You used me as bait.{\r}

694
01:11:54,646 --> 01:11:56,375
你还和我做爱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And you made love to me.{\r}

695
01:11:58,283 --> 01:11:59,215
为什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

696
01:12:00,118 --> 01:12:03,485
你是在等他下次行动之前 打发时间吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}To pass the time as you waited for him to strike?{\r}

697
01:12:15,867 --> 01:12:19,268
他在输油管附近杀了十个人
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's struck again. Ten men are dead at the pipeline.{\r}

698
01:12:19,471 --> 01:12:20,335
我跟你去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm coming with you.{\r}

699
01:12:21,873 --> 01:12:24,603
随你便 我已打给M夫人了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You do what you want to do, but I've called M.{\r}

700
01:12:25,910 --> 01:12:27,901
她会来指挥大局的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She's coming to take charge.{\r}

701
01:12:57,675 --> 01:13:00,075
目前情况如何？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I want an update. Where do we stand?{\r}

702
01:13:01,012 --> 01:13:04,106
雷纳的手下 把定位晶片抽掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}One of Renard's men took the locator card from the bomb...{\r}

703
01:13:04,349 --> 01:13:05,782
无法追踪,可是…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...so we can't track it. But....{\r}

704
01:13:05,984 --> 01:13:07,212
可是什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But what?{\r}

705
01:13:07,886 --> 01:13:09,251
恕我直言
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}With all due respect...{\r}

706
01:13:10,154 --> 01:13:11,985
你不应该来的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...I don't think you should be here.{\r}

707
01:13:13,124 --> 01:13:16,457
我能提醒你我是因为你才来的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}May I remind you that you're the reason I'm here, 007.{\r}

708
01:13:16,794 --> 01:13:19,228
你违反命令 把她丢下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You disobeyed an order and left that girl alone.{\r}

709
01:13:19,430 --> 01:13:22,331
也许她没有你想像的那么无辜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Perhaps that girl isn't as innocent as you think.{\r}

710
01:13:22,534 --> 01:13:25,196
-你说什么？ -假如偷换
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-What are you saying? -Suppose the inside man...{\r}

711
01:13:25,403 --> 01:13:27,234
金恩胸针的内贼
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...the one who switched King's lapel pin...{\r}

712
01:13:28,273 --> 01:13:30,036
是个女内贼？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...turned out to be an inside woman?{\r}

713
01:13:32,944 --> 01:13:35,879
她杀死父亲,破坏自家的油管？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She kills her father and attacks her own pipeline?{\r}

714
01:13:36,080 --> 01:13:38,480
-为什么？图的是什么？ -我还不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Why? To what end? -I don't know...yet.{\r}

715
01:13:46,357 --> 01:13:47,551
你看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look at that.{\r}

716
01:13:47,759 --> 01:13:48,691
这里不太对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}That's not right.{\r}

717
01:13:50,228 --> 01:13:51,058
那是什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What is it?{\r}

718
01:13:51,262 --> 01:13:52,854
侦查车
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}An observation rig.{\r}

719
01:13:53,064 --> 01:13:55,123
在输油管内寻找裂缝
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Travels in the pipe looking for cracks.{\r}

720
01:13:55,333 --> 01:13:56,664
关掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Shut it down.{\r}

721
01:13:59,337 --> 01:14:00,235
没办法
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't understand.{\r}

722
01:14:00,438 --> 01:14:02,030
没有反应
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It won't respond.{\r}

723
01:14:02,540 --> 01:14:04,337
那地方没有炸弹,没有核弹的--
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The place is clean. No sign of--{\r}

724
01:14:04,576 --> 01:14:07,044
-核弹在输油管里 -我的天啊！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-The bomb is in the pipeline. -Oh, my God!{\r}

725
01:14:07,278 --> 01:14:10,076
他们带核弹经过这里 这解释了之前的攻击
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They brought it through here. That'd explain the attack.{\r}

726
01:14:10,281 --> 01:14:11,748
炸弹被送往主控室
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Heading for the oil terminal.{\r}

727
01:14:11,916 --> 01:14:13,781
造成最大的破坏
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Where it would do the most damage.{\r}

728
01:14:13,985 --> 01:14:15,976
叫你的员工立刻疏散
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Have your men evacuate that terminal.{\r}

729
01:14:17,889 --> 01:14:19,288
你相信我了吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So now do you believe me?{\r}

730
01:14:22,026 --> 01:14:24,392
这是紧急状况
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}This is an emergency situation. So please...{\r}

731
01:14:24,862 --> 01:14:26,693
请立刻疏散
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...clear the room. Do it.{\r}

732
01:14:26,898 --> 01:14:28,229
他想要破坏输油管
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's going for the oil.{\r}

733
01:14:29,133 --> 01:14:33,229
这是西方未来唯一的输油管
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The one pipeline the West is counting on to supply our reserves.{\r}

734
01:14:34,339 --> 01:14:35,601
你有办法吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you have an idea?{\r}

735
01:14:35,807 --> 01:14:36,865
也许吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe.{\r}

736
01:14:37,976 --> 01:14:41,002
炸弹有多远？ 速度有多快？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How far is the rig from the terminal? How fast is it traveling?{\r}

737
01:14:41,546 --> 01:14:45,949
它在106哩外 时速70哩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's 1 06 miles from the terminal, going 70 miles an hour.{\r}

738
01:14:46,217 --> 01:14:48,185
有78分钟 还有侦查车吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We have 78 minutes. Is there another rig?{\r}

739
01:14:48,386 --> 01:14:51,082
在炸弹前面有一辆
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's one parked in the passageway ahead of it.{\r}

740
01:14:51,356 --> 01:14:54,086
-你能带我去吗？ -当然
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Charles, can you get me out there? -Of course.{\r}

741
01:14:55,259 --> 01:14:57,955
慢着,你要去做的 是我想你要去做的吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Wait. Are you gonna do what I think you're gonna do?{\r}

742
01:14:58,162 --> 01:15:01,359
-拆除核弹需要什么？ -我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-What do I need to defuse a bomb? -Me.{\r}

743
01:15:14,112 --> 01:15:14,942
在这儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There it is.{\r}

744
01:15:15,580 --> 01:15:17,377
闸门在那儿
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Hatch to the passageway.{\r}

745
01:15:21,853 --> 01:15:25,016
你来操控 试着让炸弹赶上我们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You keep the speed up so the other rig catches up with us.{\r}

746
01:15:25,223 --> 01:15:26,850
-我会等你的消息 -好
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-I'll wait to hear from you. -Gotcha.{\r}

747
01:15:28,159 --> 01:15:29,786
你会开这玩意吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You know how to drive this thing?{\r}

748
01:15:29,994 --> 01:15:33,122
开这玩意不需要博士学位
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Doesn't exactly take a degree in nuclear physics.{\r}

749
01:15:41,506 --> 01:15:42,996
他们进了输油管
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They're in the pipeline.{\r}

750
01:15:43,641 --> 01:15:45,131
他们出发了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}They're on the move.{\r}

751
01:16:01,392 --> 01:16:02,586
快一点！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Faster!{\r}

752
01:16:10,435 --> 01:16:12,926
只要有丝毫的机会 庞德就会成功
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}If there's the slightest chance, Bond will succeed.{\r}

753
01:16:13,738 --> 01:16:15,296
他是最顶尖的情报员
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He's the best we have...{\r}

754
01:16:15,840 --> 01:16:17,467
不过我都没告诉过他
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...though I'd never tell him.{\r}

755
01:16:18,810 --> 01:16:20,505
希望你说得对
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope you're right.{\r}

756
01:16:24,082 --> 01:16:25,413
它来了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Here it comes!{\r}

757
01:16:29,520 --> 01:16:31,681
赶上来了,快一点！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's closing up. Faster!{\r}

758
01:16:37,328 --> 01:16:38,818
坐稳了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Sit tight.{\r}

759
01:16:54,245 --> 01:16:56,236
停不下来！刹车卡住了！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}No brakes! The controls are jammed!{\r}

760
01:17:10,695 --> 01:17:12,663
这是战略性弹头
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's a tactical fission device.{\r}

761
01:17:12,864 --> 01:17:14,889
威力不大,稳住了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Low yield. Hold me steady.{\r}

762
01:17:15,666 --> 01:17:17,634
你拆过几百个,对吧？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You've defused hundreds of these, right?{\r}

763
01:17:17,835 --> 01:17:20,360
对,但不在这种情况下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, but they're usually standing still.{\r}

764
01:17:21,606 --> 01:17:24,040
生命充满了挑战
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Life's full of small challenges.{\r}

765
01:17:25,243 --> 01:17:26,210
你看
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Have a look at this.{\r}

766
01:17:26,577 --> 01:17:28,044
螺丝头不见了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Someone stripped the screw heads.{\r}

767
01:17:29,947 --> 01:17:32,108
有人动过这枚核弹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Someone's tampered with the bomb.{\r}

768
01:17:52,136 --> 01:17:54,798
一半的钸元素不见了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, half the plutonium's missing.{\r}

769
01:17:55,606 --> 01:17:58,200
你的意思是什么？ 它不能引起核爆吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So what are you saying? It couldn't go nuclear?{\r}

770
01:17:58,442 --> 01:18:02,208
如果被引爆还是能炸死我们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}There's still enough explosive to kill us both if the trigger goes off.{\r}

771
01:18:02,647 --> 01:18:04,342
-让它爆炸 -我可以拆除
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Let it blow. -But I can stop it.{\r}

772
01:18:04,549 --> 01:18:05,538
让它爆炸！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Let it blow!{\r}

773
01:18:11,889 --> 01:18:12,981
相信我,别管它
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Trust me. Leave it.{\r}

774
01:18:17,128 --> 01:18:18,891
过去,过去！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Move down. Move down!{\r}

775
01:18:19,163 --> 01:18:20,323
快跳！跳！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Jump! Go on, jump!{\r}

776
01:18:23,568 --> 01:18:24,398
快！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Jump!{\r}

777
01:18:39,217 --> 01:18:40,878
罗宾森报告说
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Robinson's reporting.{\r}

778
01:18:41,385 --> 01:18:43,353
这不是核弹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The bomb was a dud.{\r}

779
01:18:44,388 --> 01:18:47,789
不过引爆还是能毁坏 一段50英尺长的油管
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But the triggering charge blew out a 50-yard section of the pipe.{\r}

780
01:18:47,992 --> 01:18:49,084
庞德呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And Bond?{\r}

781
01:18:50,161 --> 01:18:51,150
没消息
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing.{\r}

782
01:18:52,997 --> 01:18:54,521
很遗憾
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm so sorry.{\r}

783
01:18:57,435 --> 01:18:59,164
不过我有礼物要送你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But I have a gift for you.{\r}

784
01:18:59,971 --> 01:19:02,098
先父的遗物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Something that belonged to my father.{\r}

785
01:19:02,707 --> 01:19:04,436
他会希望你收下
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He would've wanted you to have it.{\r}

786
01:19:05,576 --> 01:19:06,873
现在不是时候
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Perhaps this isn't the time.{\r}

787
01:19:07,879 --> 01:19:09,039
求求你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Please.{\r}

788
01:19:10,348 --> 01:19:13,511
他经常提到
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He often spoke of how compassionately...{\r}

789
01:19:13,851 --> 01:19:17,981
我被绑架时 你给他最真诚的建议
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...you advised him on the best course of action during my kidnapping.{\r}

790
01:19:21,759 --> 01:19:23,420
这是非常宝贵的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's very valuable, you know.{\r}

791
01:19:24,262 --> 01:19:26,822
我不想把胸针也炸掉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I couldn't let it explode with the rest of him.{\r}

792
01:19:32,169 --> 01:19:35,366
很可惜那笔钱 没把你也给炸死
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I was very upset when the money didn't kill both of you.{\r}

793
01:19:36,107 --> 01:19:38,439
我以为没有机会了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't think I'd get another chance.{\r}

794
01:19:39,310 --> 01:19:42,507
后来你却自己把机会送上门
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Then you dropped the answer right in my lap.{\r}

795
01:19:43,147 --> 01:19:44,079
庞德
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bond.{\r}

796
01:19:44,649 --> 01:19:47,482
你也说他是最顶尖的
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And as you say, he's the best you have.{\r}

797
01:19:47,685 --> 01:19:49,710
那是过去式了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Or should I say, ''had''?{\r}

798
01:19:56,093 --> 01:19:57,617
把她带上直升机
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Take her to the helicopter.{\r}

799
01:20:04,502 --> 01:20:05,833
把手给我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, give me your hand.{\r}

800
01:20:06,037 --> 01:20:07,231
跳,跳！
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Jump, jump!{\r}

801
01:20:08,706 --> 01:20:10,640
你为什么这么做？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you wanna explain why you did that?{\r}

802
01:20:10,875 --> 01:20:13,366
我能拆除的 你差点害死我们
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I could've stopped it. You almost killed us.{\r}

803
01:20:13,611 --> 01:20:15,010
我们是死了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I did kill us.{\r}

804
01:20:15,646 --> 01:20:18,911
她以为我们死了 她的诡计就得逞
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She thinks we're dead, and she thinks she got away with it.{\r}

805
01:20:19,116 --> 01:20:22,552
我不是间谍 请你白话一点
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you wanna put that in English for those of us who don't speak ''spy''?{\r}

806
01:20:22,753 --> 01:20:23,845
你在说谁？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Who's ''she''?{\r}

807
01:20:24,055 --> 01:20:25,215
伊莉翠金恩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Elektra King.{\r}

808
01:20:25,423 --> 01:20:27,550
她干嘛要炸掉自己的输油管？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why would she blow up her own pipeline?{\r}

809
01:20:27,758 --> 01:20:29,248
为了证明她的无辜
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It makes her look innocent.{\r}

810
01:20:31,095 --> 01:20:34,087
爆炸掩饰钸元素遭窃的事实
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The explosion covers up the theft of the plutonium.{\r}

811
01:20:35,599 --> 01:20:37,260
使人误为恐怖份子攻击
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It looks like a terrorist attack.{\r}

812
01:20:37,468 --> 01:20:39,698
但为什么留下这一半钸元素？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But why leave this half?{\r}

813
01:20:40,071 --> 01:20:43,700
留下这些钸元素 才能掩饰他们偷走的另一半
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So there's enough to spread around to cover up what they did take.{\r}

814
01:20:43,908 --> 01:20:45,933
他们拿另一半干嘛？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What will they do with the other half?{\r}

815
01:20:46,177 --> 01:20:48,611
这分量做不出核弹
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not enough to make a nuclear bomb.{\r}

816
01:20:48,813 --> 01:20:51,577
-你是专家,你解释给我听 -我不知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-You're the scientist, you tell me. -I don't know.{\r}

817
01:20:52,683 --> 01:20:56,016
天下最凶狠的恐怖份子 偷走六公斤的钸元素
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But the world's greatest terrorist running around with 6 kilos...{\r}

818
01:20:56,220 --> 01:20:57,847
不会干好事
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...of plutonium can't be good.{\r}

819
01:20:58,055 --> 01:21:00,523
我不拿回来 就会被打屁股
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have to get it back, or somebody will have my ass.{\r}

820
01:21:03,294 --> 01:21:04,693
那个以后再说
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}First things first.{\r}

821
01:21:06,931 --> 01:21:08,865
呼叫罗宾逊,收到吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bond to Robinson. Do you copy?{\r}

822
01:21:09,066 --> 01:21:11,899
对了 跟你合作之前
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}By the way, before we go any further...{\r}

823
01:21:12,269 --> 01:21:13,827
我想先知道
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...I just wanna know....{\r}

824
01:21:14,672 --> 01:21:17,072
你跟伊莉翠有什么关系？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's the story with you and Elektra?{\r}

825
01:21:17,308 --> 01:21:19,936
现在只有敌对关系
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}We're strictly platonic. Now.{\r}

826
01:21:20,177 --> 01:21:22,372
罗宾逊,收到吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Bond to Robinson. Copy?{\r}

827
01:21:24,749 --> 01:21:26,148
你呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What's your story?{\r}

828
01:21:26,717 --> 01:21:28,844
你怎么会跑到哈萨克？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing here in Kazakhstan?{\r}

829
01:21:29,053 --> 01:21:32,113
跟你一样 逃避这些问题
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Avoiding those kind of questions, just like you.{\r}

830
01:21:32,690 --> 01:21:35,250
我收到了,紧急状况
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I read you, 007. Red alert.{\r}

831
01:21:35,459 --> 01:21:37,518
M夫人跟伊莉翠一起失踪了 还有三人挂彩
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}M is missing with Elektra. Three men down.{\r}

832
01:21:37,728 --> 01:21:39,628
等待指示
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Await instructions. Out.{\r}

833
01:21:41,298 --> 01:21:42,287
我们该怎么办？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What do we do now?{\r}

834
01:21:46,804 --> 01:21:49,170
我忘了一件很关键的事
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I may have overlooked one critical element.{\r}

835
01:21:49,473 --> 01:21:51,407
是什么？更多钸元素吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What? More plutonium?{\r}

836
01:21:52,309 --> 01:21:53,367
不是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Beluga.{\r}

837
01:21:54,145 --> 01:21:55,510
俄制鱼子酱
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Caviar.{\r}

838
01:21:56,814 --> 01:22:00,648
伊斯坦堡,土耳其
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}{\r}

839
01:22:25,176 --> 01:22:26,507
你带什么给我？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Brought me something?{\r}

840
01:22:32,550 --> 01:22:34,814
改变世界的力量
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The power to reshape the world.{\r}

841
01:22:38,289 --> 01:22:39,278
拿去
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Go on.{\r}

842
01:22:40,024 --> 01:22:41,048
很安全
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's safe.{\r}

843
01:22:42,593 --> 01:22:44,220
感觉一下你的未来
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Touch your destiny.{\r}

844
01:22:57,875 --> 01:23:00,400
我也带了礼物给你
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I have brought something for you as well.{\r}

845
01:23:06,884 --> 01:23:08,579
你的礼物
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your present.{\r}

846
01:23:08,853 --> 01:23:11,413
都是死去的庞德的心意
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Courtesy of the late Mr. Bond.{\r}

847
01:23:12,156 --> 01:23:13,384
下令处死我的凶手
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}My executioner.{\r}

848
01:23:13,791 --> 01:23:15,725
可惜没把你杀死
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Overpraise, I'm afraid.{\r}

849
01:23:16,193 --> 01:23:19,094
-我的手下会解决你的 -你的手下？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-But my people will finish the job. -Your people?{\r}

850
01:23:19,663 --> 01:23:22,598
他们会让你在此自生自灭
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Your people will leave you here to rot...{\r}

851
01:23:23,367 --> 01:23:25,426
就像你对我一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...just like you left me.{\r}

852
01:23:26,003 --> 01:23:27,300
你还有我父亲
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You and my father.{\r}

853
01:23:27,505 --> 01:23:29,564
-你父亲… -他什么都不是
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}-Your father-- -My father was nothing.{\r}

854
01:23:30,207 --> 01:23:32,698
他偷走我母亲的石油王国
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}His kingdom he stole from my mother.{\r}

855
01:23:33,811 --> 01:23:36,712
我要夺回我的王国
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}The kingdom I will rightly take back.{\r}

856
01:23:45,489 --> 01:23:47,957
你把她变成这样很得意吧
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope you're proud of what you did to her.{\r}

857
01:23:49,226 --> 01:23:51,694
这是你的功劳
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm afraid it is you who deserve credit.{\r}

858
01:23:53,364 --> 01:23:54,763
当时的她
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}When I took her...{\r}

859
01:23:55,299 --> 01:23:57,290
真是天真无邪
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...she was promise itself.{\r}

860
01:23:57,968 --> 01:24:00,562
你却把她推入我这个火坑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You left her at the mercy of a man like me.{\r}

861
01:24:01,739 --> 01:24:03,366
你毁了她
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You ruined her.{\r}

862
01:24:04,108 --> 01:24:04,904
为了什么？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}For what?{\r}

863
01:24:05,409 --> 01:24:06,740
只为了逮到我？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}To get to me?{\r}

864
01:24:07,344 --> 01:24:08,936
她比我好太多了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}She's worth 50 of me.{\r}

865
01:24:09,180 --> 01:24:11,114
这点我很同意
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}For once, I agree with you.{\r}

866
01:24:15,019 --> 01:24:17,544
现在我们的命运相同
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And now we also share a common fate.{\r}

867
01:24:18,322 --> 01:24:19,152
你会跟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}You will die...{\r}

868
01:24:19,857 --> 01:24:21,882
这城市的人一起丧命
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...along with everyone in this city...{\r}

869
01:24:23,460 --> 01:24:27,521
西方国家的未来 也会毁于一旦
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...and the bright, starry, oil-driven future of the West.{\r}

870
01:24:34,038 --> 01:24:36,268
自从你派人刺杀我
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Since you sent your man to kill me...{\r}

871
01:24:36,574 --> 01:24:39,099
我就一直看着时钟 分分秒秒在走
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...I've been watching time tick slowly away...{\r}

872
01:24:40,177 --> 01:24:42,270
走向我的灭亡
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...marching toward my own death.{\r}

873
01:24:45,916 --> 01:24:48,009
现在你也一样
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Now you can have the same pleasure.{\r}

874
01:24:52,156 --> 01:24:53,885
我要你看着时钟
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Watch these hands, M.{\r}

875
01:24:54,959 --> 01:24:56,654
明天正午
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}By noon tomorrow...{\r}

876
01:24:57,361 --> 01:24:58,623
就是你的死期
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...your time is up.{\r}

877
01:25:00,364 --> 01:25:02,059
我向你保证
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}And I guarantee you...{\r}

878
01:25:02,466 --> 01:25:04,093
我绝不会错过
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}...I will not miss.{\r}

879
01:25:26,757 --> 01:25:28,281
你好美
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So beautiful.{\r}

880
01:25:29,893 --> 01:25:31,292
好光滑
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So smooth.{\r}

881
01:25:32,696 --> 01:25:34,129
好温暖
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}So warm.{\r}

882
01:25:35,065 --> 01:25:36,555
你怎么知道？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}How would you know?{\r}

883
01:25:41,905 --> 01:25:43,338
你为什么要这样？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Why are you like this?{\r}

884
01:25:44,708 --> 01:25:46,505
因为庞德死了？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Because Bond is dead?{\r}

885
01:25:47,845 --> 01:25:49,369
你不是要他死吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}It's what you wanted.{\r}

886
01:25:50,581 --> 01:25:52,515
当然了
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course it's what I wanted.{\r}

887
01:25:57,655 --> 01:25:58,781
他…
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was....{\r}

888
01:26:02,092 --> 01:26:03,389
他是好情人吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}He was a good lover?{\r}

889
01:26:04,261 --> 01:26:05,694
你说呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you think?{\r}

890
01:26:05,896 --> 01:26:07,887
难道我没感觉吗？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I wouldn't feel anything?{\r}

891
01:26:22,513 --> 01:26:23,980
我一点都没有感觉
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}I feel nothing.{\r}

892
01:26:40,064 --> 01:26:41,656
这样呢？
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}What about this?{\r}

893
01:26:52,476 --> 01:26:53,943
你一定
{\fscx75\fscy75\1c&H00FFFF&}But surely...{\r}

894
01:26:55,012 --> 01:26:58,106
会感觉到这吧？
